The '''Hungary national under-17 football team''' represents [[Hungary]] in [[association football]] at under-17 age level and is controlled by the [[Hungarian Football Association]], the governing body for football in Hungary. The current manager is of the team is [[Ferenc Bene, Jr.]], the son of former legendary forward [[Ferenc Bene]].
==Team== ===Current squad=== The following players were named in the squad for the [[2011 UEFA European Under-17 Football Championship elite round|European Championship Elite Qualifying Round]] matches against [[Russia national under-17 football team|Russia]] on 24 March, [[Iceland national under-17 football team|Iceland]] on 26 March, and [[Romania national under-17 football team|Romania]] on 29 March 2011.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mlsz.hu/cikkek/u17/2011/03/21/vegleges-az-u17-es-valogatott-kerete|title=VÃ©gleges az U17-es vÃ¡logatott kerete|publisher=[[Hungarian Football Federation]] |date=21 March 2011|accessdate=25 March 2011}}</ref>
